Canning feels natural to Maria because she grew up
working in the fields in Puerto Rico. She arrived in
New York more than 50 years ago, and she still calls
South Williamsburg “Los Sures”. She began picking up
cans and bottles in the late nineties, after losing her
job in a clothing factory. Maria believes that anyone
can make a living in New York. She thinks that it’s
